               <head>Miscellany</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Miscellany</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85109233 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100084" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15689-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8205">Miscellany</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A collection of miscellaneous works. Some are in verse, some in prose; while most are in Persian, some of the verse is in Pashto. </p>
                        <p>The contents of this collection can be summarized as follows: 1r: Persian verses; 1v-3r: the opening of a work in Persian in mixed verse and prose; 3v: a rubā‘ī (quatrain rhyming AABA) in Persian; 4r: the opening of a prose work in Arabic; 4v-8v: a poem or poems in Persian, the band (refrain) of each stanza being in Pashto; 9r-36v: the first part of a Persian commentary on the Masnavī-’i ma‘navī of Jalāl al-Dīn Rūmī; 37r, 38r-40r: verses in Pashto; those on 37v are written vertically; 40v: blank but for some lines of writing that have been erased; 41r: part of a letter in Persian, not apparently related to other material in the manuscript; 41r-v: verses in Pashto. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara pus">Persian and Pashto with some Arabic</textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
